  "prompt": "How do I write a very short summary of Hamlet?",
  "response": "Writing a very short summary of **Hamlet** involves distilling the play's complex plot, themes, and characters into a concise overview. Here are some steps to help you create an effective summary:\n\n1. **Identify the Main Plot Points:**\n   - **Prince Hamlet** seeks to avenge his father's murder.\n   - He grapples with indecision and feigns madness.\n   - The play culminates in a tragic climax where most main characters, including Hamlet, die.\n\n2. **Highlight Key Characters:**\n   - **Hamlet:** The protagonist struggling with revenge and moral integrity.\n   - **King Claudius:** Hamlet\u2019s uncle and the antagonist who has usurped the throne.\n   - **Ophelia:** Hamlet\u2019s love interest, representing innocence and tragedy.\n\n3. **Focus on Central Themes:**\n   - Revenge and justice\n   - Madness (both real and feigned)\n   - Mortality and the human condition\n\n4. **Be Concise and Clear:**\n   - Use simple language.\n   - Keep the summary to a few sentences.\n\n**Example of a Very Short Summary:**\n\n*In Shakespeare's \"Hamlet,\" Prince Hamlet seeks to avenge his father's murder by his uncle, King Claudius. Struggling with doubt and feigning madness, Hamlet's quest leads to a tragic series of events, resulting in the deaths of most main characters, including himself.*\n\nThis summary captures the essence of the play by mentioning the main character, his objective, key conflicts, and the outcome, all in a succinct manner.",
